   GLOBAL-MANAGERS (Undated) _ Every year, untold thousands of U.S.
executives arrive home from foreign assignments and then bolt to
greener pastures, often at a cost to their employers of $1 million
or more that has been invested in training and overseas expenses.
Twenty-five percent of returning managers leave their employers
within a year, according to one expert _ double the proportion of
their stay-at-home colleagues. By Jobert E. Abueva.
