<SLUG> BC-LEAH-PERSONALS-SFCHRON </SLUG>
  
 PERSONALS: What's Love Got to Do With It?
<TEXT>
<P>
   &UR; (Eds: This story also moved in the ``l'' lifestyle news
file.) &QL;  &LR; 
 &UR; By LEAH GARCHIK &QC;  &LR; 
 &UR; c.2000, San Francisco Chronicle &LR;  &QC; 
Hearing Dogs for Hearing People, a British charity of
which &UR; Princess Anne &LR;  is patron, has mated a Chihuahua and a
Labrador retriever in an effort to create ``small, good-natured
dogs for deaf people,'' the group's  &UR; Lisa Wigmore &LR;  told the Times
of London. It is not known how the group hoped to avoid creating a
large nervous dog instead.
</P>
<P>
   The union of the two breeds was accomplished by boosting the
male Chihuahua on top of two large bags of dog biscuits. The six
puppies that resulted are 5 months old.
</P>
<P>
   Some human animal lovers are not pleased at this love story.
``It's just unnatural,'' said  &UR; Diana Fitt-Savage &LR;  of the British
Chihuahua Club. ``One vet who heard about it told me: `It's a
wonder they didn't lose the Chihuahua''' (presumably from taking a
fall).
</P>
<P>
   Both dogs, described by Wigmore as a ``small, light-boned''
Labrador and an ``oversized'' Chihuahua, belonged to staff members
of the charity, says a story forwarded to Personals by
 &UR; Mark Steinberg &LR; .
</P>
<P>
   In a related observation, dog expert  &UR; Elizabeth Marshall &LR; , whose
latest book is ``The Social Life of Dogs'' (Simon &AMP; Schuster; $24),
takes to task ``dog fascists'' who believe that all mongrels are
bad. ``The very existence of a mongrel means that someone got to
choose her own mate,'' says free-love proponent Marshall. ``The
notion of racial purity is not of course confined to dogs. Yet it
is destructive wherever one finds it.'' Marshall will be at Book
Passage in Corte Madera on June 13.
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
 &UR; FLASH &LR;
</P>
<P>
   _MSNBC says that  &UR; Mariah Carey &LR;  _ no chopped liver, she _
exploded with rage at the World Music Awards ceremony in Monaco
last week when fellow honoree  &UR; Michael Jackson &LR;  was introduced
``amid a cloud of dry-ice smoke while a video montage of his career
and a large silhouette of him was projected on the stage,'' and
 &UR; Prince Albert &LR;  gave him an award.
</P>
<P>
   _Foreign affairs expert  &UR; Goldie Hawn &LR;  was at the Capitol last
week lobbying against normalizing trade relations with China,
reports Roll Call.
</P>
<P>
   _Freelance writer  &UR; Burt Dragin &LR;  sent for the writers' guidelines
for Singapore Airlines' in-flight magazine. Contributors are asked
to ``Avoid: Any mention of death, air crashes or sex.''
</P>
<P>
   &UR; ROCKY RETURNS? &LR;
</P>
<P>
   Entertainment Weekly reports that  &UR; Sylvester Stallone &LR;  has
written another ``Rocky'' script and is hoping to sell it to MGM.
``We need at least 20 or 22 million dollars to do it,'' he said.
``I mean, you've got to pay  &UR; Talia Shire &LR;  something.''
</P>
<P>
   Meanwhile, at the premiere for ``Center Stage,''  &UR; Burt Young &LR; ,
who played Paulie in the ``Rocky'' movies, told  &UR; Baird Jones &LR;  that
