SAN FRANCISCO _  SECRETS-SALAD  _ Pairing fruit and savory
ingredients is a difficult challenge. Montage chef Jennifer Cox
succeeds in creating a delicious salad of strawberries, watercress,
toasted almonds and creamy fromage blanc. &HT;    This is the latest installment of the regular column describing
what makes a Bay Area restaurant's dish a success, we'll tell how
to make it.
 &HT;    With chef's secrets for success, recipe.
 &HT;     By Michael Bauer  
 c. 1999 The San Francisco Chronicle  
<TEXT>
 &QL; 
 &QL; 
SAN FRANCISCO _  &UR; LEARN-CHEESE &LR;  _ Every home cook worth his or her
salt has a couple of favorite concoctions waiting to be used in
case of unexpected guests, or just to improve a rather spartan
