<P>
   &UR; INTERNATIONAL (i) &LR;
</P>
<P>
   IRELAND-PEACE (Belfast) _ Boston plays a key role in an unusual
partnership that has produced a breakthrough in Northern Ireland's
peace effort. By Kevin Cullen. 1400 words.
</P>
<P>
   MIDEAST-YOUTH (Bethlehem) _ Most of their lives they've had the
progress _ or lack of progress _ in Israeli-Palestinian peace talks
in the background. But youths in the region have a life to live,
and little tolerance for the incremental stuff unless negotiators
get something going. By Aliza Marcus. 900 words.
</P>
<P>
   &UR;  &LR;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; NATIONAL (a) &LR;
</P>
<P>
   RELIGION-CHARISMATIC (Waltham, Mass.) _ Twice a week, hundreds
of people from all over New England flock to worship services led
by Father Tom DiLorenzo of Holy Rosary Church. They sing, dance,
speak in tongues, have visions and fall to the ground, ``slain in
the spirit. As odd as Father Tom's style may seem to most
Catholics, it is part of a ``charismatic renewal'' movement that
American bishops say will be a key to the strength of the Church in
the 21st century. By Marcella Bombardieri. 1200 words. PHOTO
</P>
