</P>
<P>
   POKER-CHAMPIONSHIPS ((Las Vegas) _ The world's best poker
players are gathered in the poker room of Binion's Horseshoe Casino
for the World Series of Poker. The best of the best are here; the
meek, if they are wise, should check their wallets at the cashier's
window. By Michael Madden. (2 takes)
</P>
<P>
   RAC-PREAKNESS (Baltimore) -- Actions speak louder than words,
and Fusaichi Pegasus was so impressive winning the Kentucky Derby
that most of the trainers who ran a horse in the Derby shut up
rather than show up for the second leg of the Triple Crown. By Ron
Indrisano.
</P>
<P>
   SHAUGHNESSY-COLUMN (New York) _ Picked up pieces from the land
of Rudy, Rocket, and Latrell ... By Dan Shaughnessy.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; The Boston Globe &LR;  &QC;
</P>
