<P>
   Editors:
</P>
<P>
   The honors thesis that Brooke Ellison presented earlier this
spring at Harvard University, ``The Element of Hope in Resilient
Adolescents,'' was a scientific analysis steeped in data. But her
own story would have made a good case study.
</P>
<P>
   Struck by a car on her first day in the seventh grade and given
little chance of survival, Ellison awoke after 36 hours in a coma
as a quadriplegic.
</P>
<P>
   Though she would regain no sensation below her neck, Ellison
never missed a grade, and early next month she will cap her
improbable educational odyssey by graduating from Harvard with an
A- average and a bachelor's degree in psychology and biology.
</P>
<P>
   We have moved the following selection of photos by photographer
Evan Richman:
</P>
<P>
   NYT9, Ellison with her mother Jean on campus at Harvard.
</P>
