<HEADLINE>
&HT;     DEMOCRATS DECRY EFFORT TO BAR HISPANIC LAWYER FROM APPELLATE
BENCH 
</HEADLINE>
   &HT;     (EDS: Subs 7graf, However, to add that Moreno declined to
comment; pickup: They cited)  
 &HT;     (For use by New York Times News Service clients.)  
 &HT;     By PEGGY FIKAC  
 &HT;     c.2000 San Antonio Express-News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   EL PASO, Texas _ It's an American success story on the verge of
getting even better until, some say, it ran into the reality of
American politics.
</P>
<P>
   The story is classic: The Mexico-born son of immigrant parents
graduates from Harvard, goes home to El Paso, forges a successful
legal career and makes this far West Texas border city proud when
the president nominates him to a seat on the 5th U.S. Circuit Court
of Appeals.
</P>
<P>
   There, the story of Enrique Moreno hits a roadblock. Some blame
the twist in the plot on the politics of this presidential election
