</P>
<P>
   So, has the Internet reduced Philip Marlowe's job to a series of
clicks on a home computer?
</P>
<P>
   Take my old job of skiptracing. It's no longer hard work
tracking down a fugitive's ex-neighbors to ask about his sudden
departure. Recently, working as a reporter, I used the Internet to
collect tenants' names and phone numbers for an entire New York
