<P>
   BRUSHFIRE-THREAT (Los Angeles) _ Fearing a wildfire of New
Mexico proportions, leaders of several San Fernando Valley
homeowners groups call for year-round deployment of the
Superscooper airplane. Firefighters said the water-dropping plane
would have been ineffective in Los Alamos because of high winds,
which is why Los Angeles also relies on helicopters, which are
deployed year-round. Firefighters predicted this year's fire season
will be the worst in years. By Lisa Van Proyen. (Will move in the
``a'' national and ``n'' California news files.)
</P>
<P>
   POLANCO-SCHOOLS (Los Angeles) _ Presented with a watered-down
