panel said Wednesday they would probably vote for SB 2071 by state
Sen. Richard Polanco, D-Los Angeles. The bill would give the
monitor power over the system's personnel, policies and $7 billion
budget. By David R. Baker. (Will move in the ``n'' California news
wire.)
</P>
<P>
   NIEVES-TRIAL (Los Angeles) _ The son of Sandi Nieves testified
that she sealed the windows of their Santa Clarita home, held a
slumber party for her children in the kitchen and then set the
house on fire, killing his four sisters. When the girls complained
about the smoke, Nieves told them to get back into their sleeping
bags and not to go outside because the smoke was coming from there,
the son told jurors. By Jesse Hiestand. (Will move in the ``a''
national and ``n'' California news files.)
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
