hurdle blocking legislation that would boost the number of visas
for foreigners with technical skills such as computer programmers
and electrical engineers. The hurdle, a measure that would have
granted amnesty to between 1 million and 2 million undocumented
immigrants, was cast aside, and the House Judiciary Committee
approves the bill _ sponsored by Rep. Lamar Smith, R-Texas _ that
would end limits on such visas, known as H1-Bs. By MARK HELM.
(Already filed.)
</P>
