<P>
   BOMB-PLOT (Undated) _ President Clinton says the plot to set off
bombs at millennium celebrations in the United States, which caused
nervous Seattle officials to cancel a public event at the Space
Needle, has been tied to Osama bin Laden.
</P>
<P>
   By Scott Sunde. (Story has moved in the ``a'' category.)
</P>
<P>
   BUSH-CHINA (Everett, Wash.) _ In a speech at a Boeing plant,
Republican presidential candidate George W. Bush urges Congress to
grant permanent normal trade relations to China.
</P>
<P>
   By Paul Nyhan. (Story will move in the ``a'' category.)
</P>
<P>
   TV-CBS (Undated) _ It was CBS's turn Wednesday to unveil a new
prime-time lineup for next fall, and the network whose viewers tend
to be older than any other's offered up little in the way of new
and different. More like tried and true.
</P>
<P>
   By John Levesque. (Story has moved in the ``e'' category.)
</P>
