<SLUG> BC-NYTIMES-PRIZE-NYT </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
TIMES WRITER WINS AWARD FOR EUROPEAN REPORTING 
</HEADLINE>
  c.2000 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   One of the few American journalists to have spent almost all of
last year in the war zones of Serbia and Kosovo, Steven Erlanger of
The New York Times, has won an award for European reporting from
the German Marshall Fund of the United States.
</P>
<P>
   The Peter Weitz Prize, worth $10,000, rewards excellence and
originality in reporting and analyzing European and transatlantic
affairs. A runner-up prize went to a team from Business Week, which
reported on Europe 10 years after the Berlin Wall fell.
</P>
<P>
   The German Marshall Fund was begun in 1972 with a gift from the
German people, as a way to commemorate the postwar Marshall Plan.
</P>
</TEXT>
